<HEADLINE>
<P>
KING FALLS SHORT IN BID FOR NO. 30 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Betsy King will have to wait at least another week for a chance to make it to 
the LPGA Hall of Fame. 
</P>
<P>
 King, who led the Lady Keystone Open by one stroke as final-round play began 
Sunday, finished with a 73 for a three-under 213, tied for third with Val 
Skinner, two shots behind winner Elaine Crosby. Laura Davies was second. 
</P>
<P>
 King has won 29 tour victories, and her 30th will put her in the Hall of Fame. 
</P>
