<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOFTBALL; CS NORTHRIDGE, UCLA WIN TWICE, EARN REGIONAL TITLES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAIGE A. LEECH, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Cal State Northridge and UCLA softball teams advanced to the College World 
Series by winning regionals on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 It took a few hours longer than expected, but Northridge defeated Cal State 
Fullerton, 4-0, at home Sunday in the Region 3 final to earn a trip to Oklahoma 
City May 26-30, for the second consecutive year. 
</P>
<P>
 Trinity Johnson had a two-hitter as Fullerton (35-29) beat Northridge, 2-0, in 
the first game Sunday, forcing a winner-take-all championship game. 
</P>
<P>
 UCLA defeated UNLV, 2-1 and 3-2, in Columbia, S.C., to win Region 4. 
</P>
<P>
 Jennifer Parker's two-run double in the third inning of the second game gave 
third-ranked Northridge (49-8) a 2-0 lead. In the fourth inning, center fielder 
JenFleming, who went four for six on the day, hit a two-run home run. 
</P>
<P>
 "We've never been swept at home, on the road, anywhere," Fleming said 
afterward. "We've never lost two in a row. It just wasn't going to happen." 
</P>
<P>
 Northridge's Amy Windmiller (24-2) threw a three-hitter, striking out five. 
</P>
</TEXT>
