<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; PLAYERS' PARENTS CAN ATTEND SOCCER 
CLINIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A free workshop for parents interested in helping out during children's soccer 
games will be held June 12 from 2 to 5 p.m. at College View School, 6582 Lennox 
Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 The featured speaker will be John Ouellette, the American Youth Soccer 
Organization's national director of coaching. Ouellette, who is based in Utah, 
will speak on "Sportsmanship and Ethics." 
</P>
<P>
 The session is being sponsored by Region 55 of AYSO. 
</P>
<P>
 "The purpose is help (adult) volunteers, and this clinic is open to anyone, 
whether or not they live in Huntington Beach," said Carol Abdou, a 
parent-volunteer in Region 55. 
</P>
