<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; MAN HELD IN FATAL CRASH ON FREEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 21-year-old motorist was arrested on suspicion of manslaughter after his 
speeding automobile allegedly struck a minivan and caused it to roll over on 
the San Diego Freeway, ejecting a 15-year-old girl who later died, the Highway 
Patrol said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Jose Isidro Gonzales Cisneros of San Juan Capistrano was taken into custody 
after the crash at 4 p.m. Saturday north of the Ortega Highway exit, according 
to a CHP spokeswoman. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, Carolina Aparicio of Hawthorne, was a passenger in a minivan 
headed south, the spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 According to authorities, Gonzales was speeding, changing lanes rapidly and 
driving recklessly when he hit the minivan in the front, causing the van to 
roll over and eject Aparicio. 
</P>
<P>
 She was taken to Mission Hospital Regional Medical Center in Mission Viejo, 
where she died of her injuries. 
</P>
<P>
 Gonzales was arrested on suspicion of vehicular manslaughter and reckless 
driving, causing injury, the CHP spokeswoman said. He was taken to Orange 
County Jail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
