<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LAGUNA BEACH; COMMISSION SEATS OPEN TO RESIDENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LESLIE EARNEST 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Residents interested in applying for positions on the city's Arts, Open Space 
or Planning commissions have until June 16 to apply. 
</P>
<P>
 Planning commissioners are charged with reviewing the way land is used within 
the city, including making recommendations to the City Council about general 
plan amendments and zoning laws.They are paid $60 per month. 
</P>
<P>
 The arts commission advises the City Council on matters involving artistic 
endeavors in Laguna Beach. Members are paid $40 monthly. 
</P>
<P>
 Open space commissioners help preserve undeveloped areas through advance 
planning, fundraising and land management. They are also paid $40 per month. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents wishing to apply for any of these positions can pick up an 
application at the city clerk's office at City Hall. Applicants will be 
interviewed by the City Council on June 21 at 6 p.m. For more information, call 
(714) 497-0705. LESLIE EARNEST 
