<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; 4 REPORTED STABBED IN MELEE AT PARTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 25-year-old Oxnard man was listed in serious condition Sunday at St. John's 
Medical Center with multiple stab wounds after a weekend party in El Rio that 
turned violent. 
</P>
<P>
 Armando Reyes was one of four men stabbed by unknown assailants late Saturday 
after some uninvited guests entered a private party on Balboa Street and 
refused to leave, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The conditions of the other three men -- Marcario Gomez, 25; Bernabe Franco, 
23, and Jesus Garcia, 22 -- were not available from supervisors at Ventura 
County Medical Center. All are from Oxnard, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura County sheriff's investigators first reported Saturday that three men 
were shot in a gunfight during a baptismal party. Officials said Sunday, 
however, that the shots did not strike anyone, but that four men were stabbed. 
</P>
<P>
 "We've got a bunch of hurt people and a whole crowd of uncooperative victims," 
Lt. Paul Anderson said. "Initially, there were some shots, but no one was hit. 
Then out came the stilettos and they went to work." 
</P>
<P>
 Anderson said that there could be other victims from the melee, but none had 
come forward and that witnesses were reluctant to tell investigators further 
details of the incident. 
</P>
<P>
 "The investigation will continue, but we've got a whole bunch of people saying 
they don't know anything," Anderson said. 
</P>
<P>
 No arrests have been made. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators said more than 100 people were attending the baptismal before 
the fight broke out. JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
