<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; KINKO'S TO MOVE 125 WORKERS TO OXNARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kinko's Service Corp., the fast-growing international copying company, has 
announced plans to move 125 employees from its Ventura corporate headquarters 
to Oxnard. 
</P>
<P>
 The company has signed a seven-year, $4.9-million lease for three floors at 
the Oxnard Town Center office building, Kinko's executive Adrianna Foss said. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're all over each other here," Foss said. "It's helping with some of the 
gridlock." About 375 people work at the corporate office. The company plans to 
eventually expand on the Ventura site, Foss said. The 125 affected employees 
work in the accounts receivable department. They will be relocated in August or 
September, she said. 
</P>
<P>
 Including the Kinko's lease, the Oxnard Town Center building is about 90% 
leased, said Alex Woronovich of Grubb & Ellis Co., which put together the deal 
with Bedord Property Investors. That group purchased the five-story building in 
December. PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
