<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: MOORPARK; NEW SITE PLANNED FOR MAINTENANCE YARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A complicated land swap involving the state Department of Transportation, the 
city of Moorpark and a developer has been worked out, moving Caltrans' proposed 
maintenance yard away from the main entrance to the city. 
</P>
<P>
 Caltrans had planned to build a repair yard to store heavy equipment and 
trucks on Los Angeles Avenue at Moorpark Freeway.City officials said the yard 
would detract from a regional shopping mall planned for the area.  
</P>
<P>
 "It's a key location for the city," Mayor Paul Lawrason said. "It would be 
totally inappropriate to place a Caltrans yard with industrial-type equipment 
at the entrance of the city, especially when we had plans for a mall right next 
door."  
</P>
<P>
 The city sued Caltrans to block construction, forcing negotiations to relocate 
the yard. An alternative site on Fitch Avenue that is owned by a local 
developer was found. SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</TEXT>
